<h3>@ViewBag.Mission</h3>

<p>Broward Premiere League (BPL) is an adult, non-profit soccer league created to provide a platform for traditional and intermediate soccer players to exercise, 
    and to improve their fitness level. It is an after work/school program designed to keep the community healthy Playing soccer is another way to do sport and stay
     healthy, as sometimes the motivation to go to the gym may not be there. The advantages of doing sport are priceless. In almost every medical malaise, if not all, 
    exercising is a way to control, retard or even prevent the attack of illnesses, as diabetes, high blood pressure, healthy heart, depression, to name a few. 
    The league provides just that medium. The age bracket is 25 and up for males; however, a team may have at least 2 players under 25 with the cut off age at 20.
     For females, the age bracket is 18 years of age. The qualifying participants may come from all walks of life that include school based employees, students, medical 
    professionals, lawyers, friends, families, or anyone who meets the criteria to be part of the friends and family league. BESL will be sensitive to foster an environment of peace, 
    violence free/tranquility, and friendly to make soccer/sport fun for all.
 </p>

<h3>@ViewBag.Philosophy</h3>
<p>
    Our philosophy is to develop good and positive rapport with the participants, to make certain their journey with the league unforgettable. 
    Transparency and respect to all will be the core to its operation. We are committed to the recreation and maintenance of a peaceful and secure 
    atmosphere, and a friendly/responsible approach to promptly resolve unforeseen circumstances. We embrace diversity and value the integrity of the individual. 
    Through the program, participants will recognize the importance to be involved in sport to stay healthy by maintaining a program of sport regiment.
</p>

<h3>@ViewBag.Tournament</h3>
<p>
    The league holds active tournaments twice a year (2/year), Fall and Spring season, and plays a maximum of 10 games per occurrence.
     Rainy game delayed is to be postponed, and the league is responsible to make arrangement with the city of plantation to make-up games not played. 
</p>

